cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it focuses on natural language processing tasks and proposes a new approach to modeling convolution filters with recurrent neural networks. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the use of neural networks for learning and decision-making. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision) as convolutional neural networks are commonly used in image processing tasks, and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it involves the use of neural networks.
